news.title: Karnataka: I-T department detects Rs 1,300 crore black income after raids on builders
news.para: "So far, the search actions have led to the detection of unaccounted income of more than Rs 1,300 crore. "Undisclosed assets in the nature of cash and gold jewellery worth more than Rs 24 crore have also been seized," the Central Board of Direct Taxes said.

news.title: BMC gets nod to not revise capital value of properties in Mumbai
news.para: The cabinet approved an amendment to Section 154(1d) of the BMC Act. Section 154(1d) allows the current value of properties to be revised once every five years.

news.title: Building codes to ensure safe EV transition in high-rises
news.para: Going by the proposals that were discussed last week, the number of e-vehicles that are allowed to park in high-rise buildings cannot be more than 20% of the total vehicles parked.

news.title: Architects can now issue OCs for houses in plotted colonies in Haryana
news.para: Officials assured that there would be random checks of the building plans and actual constructions and the architect concerned would be held accountable and even blacklisted in case of violations. But the checks would be limited to only 10% of the sites at any given time.

news.title: Blackstone-backed Nexus Select Trust files for $500 million IPO
news.para: Nexus Select Trust has a portfolio of 17 operational shopping malls across 14 major cities, covering about 10 million square feet area valued around USD 3 billion.

news.title: NCLT initiates insolvency proceedings against Ansal Properties & Infrastructures
news.para: ​A two-member bench of the insolvency tribunal had admitted the plea moved by 126 flat/villa buyers of Ansal API's real estate project "The Fernhill" located at Sector 91, Gurgaon.

news.title: In China's property crisis, global asset managers see opportunity in rental housing
news.para: The two asset managers, whose focus is on top tier Chinese cities for rental business, are in talks with distressed developers to take over assets including offices and hotels to turn them into rental housing, their executives told Reuters.

news.title: Taurus Investment Holdings & Sage Capital plan to raise Rs 500 crore to invest in Indian realty
news.para: The firms plan to focus on Tier 1 and high-growth Tier 2 cities in South and West India. The companies plan to develop a portfolio of projects worth over $1 billion over the next five years.

news.title: Evergrande eyes onshore assets as sweetener for offshore debt restructuring: Sources
news.para: Evergrande, engulfed by $300 billion in liabilities, aims to start negotiating restructuring terms next month and is combing through onshore assets to offer as additional credit enhancement to holders of its U.S. dollar-denominated bonds, the people said.

news.title: China's home prices see biggest fall in seven years, recovery bumpy
news.para: New home prices slumped 1.6% year-on-year after a 1.5% fall in September, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data on Wednesday.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Saradha Group of Companies on Dec 16
news.para: The total reserve price of these properties is pegged at about Rs 5.21 crore and the regulator has appointed C1 India as the e-auction provider.

news.title: Act against officials who issued invalid pattas: Madras HC
news.para: The Madras high court has directed the Madurai district collector to initiate departmental action against officials who had allegedly issued invalid pattas to people in Madurai district.

news.title: NCLAT rejects plea against approval of Alpha Corp's bid for Earth Infrastructure
news.para: ​National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had on June 8, 2021, approved the resolution plan from Alpha Corp Development. The Committee of Creditor (CoC) of Earth Infrastructure had voted in favour of Alpha Corp with a majority of 99 per cent.

news.title: Nagpur: To save Gorewada forest, NIT board denies residential use on 4 acre hillock
news.para: As per detailed information in the agenda of the meeting, the land is owned by Mehmuda Shikshan and Mahila Gruhnirman Vikas Bahuddeshiya Sanstha through Asma Anees Ahmed.

news.title: Revenue from property registrations jumps 50% in Chennai
news.para: Apart from the usual parts of south Chennai, areas near Porur, Koyambedu and some parts of north Chennai such as Washermenpet saw an increase in registrations.
